Description:
Mariner Innovations is actively seeking a Business Operations Coordinator/Analyst to join our growing team! The successful candidate should:

 Be a Generalist who is keen to be hands on to solve problems with tools, technology and processes that impact all areas of the business;
 Be a digitization enthusiast who has the ability to optimize business operations through understanding data and technology and how it applies to workflows from sales through to finance;
 Possess the ability to balance priorities and support decision-making of delivery team, account executives, and management team with informative data and operational processes;
 Maintain strong attention to detail and solid follow through on responsibilities to support business operations;

 Responsibilities Include:

 Build, maintain and enhance operational data, reports and, processes to enable business operations (Resource Management, Sales Operations, Human Resources, Delivery Finance, Management, etc.).
 Build and maintain an operational data dictionary, report catalogue, and process documentation.
 Work to continuously improve business operations to remove costs, improve efficiency, and make lives easier for the Mariner team.
 Ability to work with data driven technology solutions to enable operations by reporting on key business metrics.
 Operational tool licensing, administration, and reporting.

Who We Are


   International Justice Mission (IJM) is the global leader in protecting vulnerable people from violence around the world. Our global team of over 1,200 professionals are at work in 33 offices. Together, we are catalyzing a global revolution that will rescue millions, protect half a billion, and make justice unstoppable.



   Motivated by God’s call to seek justice for the oppressed, we believe that the way we work is as important as the results we achieve. We are a global community that cares for one another. We value joy and celebration, and we strive to provide professional excellence to all those we serve.



   The Need


   After almost 25 years of continued growth and operational success in pioneering the work of protecting those who are experiencing poverty from violence, IJM has become a $100+ million organization. As IJM continues this trajectory of growth and scaling of its impact, with the Vision to protect 500 million people by the year 2030, IJM’s Data & Insights team is hiring a new Business Intelligence Analyst to provide insights and actionable data to fundraising and mobilizing teams. You will work with North America team members to listen to business intelligence needs, facilitate and focus questions, and manage business intelligence projects from brainstorm to implementation. You will be challenged as part of a data & business intelligence unit that uses information every day to make key decisions about how to raise the revenue needed to rescue millions, protect half a billion and prove that justice unstoppable.



   The primary responsibility of this position is to support and deliver business intelligence and descriptive analytics to business units. The ideal candidate will be driven by discovering and documenting a business unit’s BI needs, articulating solutions to Business Operations and business units stakeholders, and presenting data and insights in a compelling way that leads to decision making. You will take pride and joy in bringing together, aligning and serving various stakeholders around a single source of truth, ensuring data is being used as a decision-support mechanism, and seeing business intelligence adoption scale exponentially within the North America region.



 This position may be based in the Washington D.C. area or may be remote in the US or Canada and reports to the Sr. Manager, Business
Intelligence
& Analytics.



   Responsibilities




     Responsible for business intelligence adoption across all North America teams;



     Scoping work with business teams to brainstorm, design, test and implement data-informed tools and processes;



     Train North American staff on how to use data visualizations and business intelligence tools;



     Disseminate business intelligence and data on projects during close out phase of project process;



     Meet Business Intelligence performance standards in SLA; and



     Build relationships with key Audience Owners with the goal to provide consistent flow of actionable insights.




   Requirements:




     Bachelor’s degree and at least three years of experience in a fast-paced professional environment, preferably in fundraising, advancement or development;



     Proven ability to synthesize data, interpret information and communicate compelling and noteworthy information to internal clients;



     Experience with data visualization tools (PowerBI and/or Tableau) preferred;



     Knowledge of R, Python, SOQL and/or SQL preferred;



     Minimum of 1-2 years working with Salesforce CRM or transferable skills with another CRM/DMS;



     Comfortable communicating complex information, including wins and failures, to stakeholders and to large groups; and



     Ability to lead brainstorm sessions that lead towards a well defined product design and program management.




   Critical Qualities:




     Mature orthodox Christian faith as defined by the Apostles’ Creed;



     Self-starter with strong initiative;



     Disciplined with priorities;



     Strong interpersonal skills and self-awareness;



     Exceptional verbal and written communication;



     Flexible, collaborative and eager to support others;



     Effective team player who fosters collaborative environment; and



     Adept at creative problem solving.




   Upload Resume, Cover Letter & Statement of Faith* in one document.



What is a statement of faith?
 A statement of faith should describe your Christian faith and how you see it as relevant to your involvement with IJM. The statement can either be incorporated into the cover letter or submitted as a separate document and should include, at a minimum, a description of your spiritual disciplines (prayer, study, etc.) and your current fellowship or place of worship.

Be part of a community of authentic, proud and trusted people. 

 Our Heavy Vehicle Parts Division is the country's largest network. This division's banners include Traction, TW and Cadel. Servicing the transport, construction and farming sectors, we keep them moving forward. This makes for a special kind of workplace. We have the experience and strength of our 100-year legacy and the desire to always do better for our team members and clients. Our 5000 colleagues proudly serve thousands of customers every day across Canada. 

 If the hat fits, we'd be proud to have you wear it! Send us your resume and join a people-centric company with a reputation of excellence. 

 Job Description 

 The mission of the Heavy Vehicles Division's Data Integrity Department is to ensure the accuracy and effective management of data and information in the various product management, procurement, inventory, and web platforms 

 For this purpose, we are looking for an analyst to take over data review and analysis initiatives and its enrichment (correction, monitoring and maintenance of all types of data related to the sales cycle of an item: attributes, upc code, etc.) taking into account the interrelationships between the various departments concerned (operations, product management, supply, marketing, IT support, etc.). 


More specifically, you will be responsible for:
 Report and investigate any problematic situations in terms of data integrity to the different internal partners; 
Identify, define, consolidate and analyze the needed data to improve and implement adequate solutions; 
Update product assortments and ensure that all relevant information is present; 
Participate in all Division projects involving the product department and ensure that data compliance rules are taken into consideration; 
Implement and maintain the different activities' procedures, to ensure the integrity of information. 
Qualifications 


To join our team, you need:
 College diploma or university degree in one of the following fields: information management, operations management, business administration, computer science or other related field; 
Have approximately 2 to 3 years of experience in a department related to procurement or information management; 
Have a good understanding of distribution and a good knowledge of supply systems, product information management (PIM) and data analysis tools; 
Essential bilingualism, both oral and written (French and English); 
Excellent computer skills MS Office suite, including in-depth knowledge of Excel, macros, and Access databases; 
