About The Ottawa Hospital











        Inspired by research and driven by compassion!



 The Ottawa Hospital (TOH) is one of Canada’s largest learning and research multi-campus hospitals. With more than 1,100 beds and approximately 12,000 staff members, we deliver specialized care to the Eastern Ontario region.





        From the compassion of our people to the relentless pursuit of new discoveries, The Ottawa Hospital never stops seeking solutions to the most complex health-care challenges while continually engaging with the community to support our vision for better patient care.


 Working together with its research institute, the University of Ottawa, and other partners, the hospital is continually gaining national and international recognition for high-quality patient care, teaching and research, while striving to meet the needs of the culturally diverse community we serve.









      Position Information











        Are you a curious, motivated individual who enjoys analyzing data sets from different perspectives, identifying and resolving issues, and translating the results into meaningful information for decision makers? Are you interested in how a hospital works and how this activity is reflected in reporting?




         Under the supervision of the Manager of Case Costing and Statistical Reporting, the analyst will be responsible for the following:


Support the tasks of processing financial and patient activity data to deliver consistent, accurate, and timely information to the General Ledger and case costing system;
Participate in the monthly and quarterly financial statement preparation, forecasting, and reporting to the Ministry of Health;
Respond to data requests from clinical and non-clinical leaders for use in decision-making. This involves understanding end user requirements, identifying data solutions; using multiple sources of data, and presenting the data in a meaningful way to end users;
