          University degree in financial management, business administration, or health information science and a minimum of two years recent related work experience or an equivalent combination of education and experience in the health care environment;



          Strong understanding of databases;



          Experience performing data analysis summarizing results in a large complex environment (healthcare preferred);



          Experience with validating and auditing data again industry standards;



          Excellent problem solving skills;



          Strong interpersonal and influencing skills;



          Sound judgement and initiative;



          Ability to work independently and in group situations;



          Strong written and verbal communication skills;



          High level of flexibility, organizational skills, teamwork and ability to multi-task;



          Eligible to work in Canada.












      Preferred Qualifications













          Familiarity with General Ledger reporting tools (Oracle and Hyperion Smartview) for the financial and statistical data;



          Familiarity with Electronic Medical Records (Epic preferred);



          Knowledge and experience in the interpretation and application of CIHI Management Information System (MIS) Standards and/or OHRS (Ontario Healthcare Reporting Standards);



          Knowledge of the OCC (Ontario Case Costing) Standards;



          Knowledge of CIHI’s databases for the utilization of clinical resources (e.g. DAD, NACRS, OMHRS, NRS) and related grouping methodologies;



          Certification with the Canadian College of Health Information Management (CCHIM)and/or professional Accounting designation (CPA/CA/CMA/CGA);



          Familiarity with Activity-Based Costing;



          Proficiency in English and French – oral expression (advanced level) and comprehension (advanced level).












